All Classes

Class Description
App
The main class of this application, responsible for its coordination.
Drone
Our program features two types of drone - this abstract class defines their shared properties, which we would expect each potential other type of drone to incorporate as well.
EuclideanUtils
This class provides static utility methods relating to Euclidean geometry.
EuclideanUtils.Orientation
The orientation of a triplet of points A,B,C.
InputProcessor
Instances of this class are used by the App class to process the given inputs, whether they are provided directly by the user, or fetched from the file server.
JsonPointStub
This class is used to extract the defining properties of a point from the GeoJSON file corresponding to a What3Words Location.
JsonSensorStub
This class is used to extract the defining properties of a sensor from an air-quality.json file.
JsonWhat3WordsStub
This class is used to extract the defining properties of a sensor from a details.json file.
LineSegment
This class models a "line segment", the part of an (infinite) line in the 2D-plane , that starts at point A and ends at point B.
MainDrone
The MainDrone class captures the properties of the drone that is used to take the sensor readings.
OutputGenerator
Instances of this class can be used to turn the data gathered by our drone into output files.
Sensor
This class models a sensor that our drone can read.
ShadowDrone
Shadow drones are a fascinating tool that our main drone has at its disposal.
TourPlanner
The TourPlanner class solves the Travelling Salesman Problem that is induced by a list of sensors that needs to be visited in an order that is as efficient as possible.
TwoDimensionalMapObject
TwoDimensionalMapObjects are characterised by a polygon (without holes, in practice, but this is not enforced by this class) and a name.
WebServerFileFetcher
Instances of this class are directly responsible for retrieving files from the web server that is used to store data relevant to this application.
What3WordsLocation
This class captures the properties of a What 3 Words Location.
